HP SPOOFING

  1. plug in a usb to ur computer (must be 32gb or less, not more)
  2. right-click on the usb drive in windows explorer and click on "format".
  3. change file system to 'fat32', then click on start and wait.
  4. download hp loader: https://mega.nz/file/0C0mzR7T#Ljl83XBVBlvFayHtfZ3dU5aqeO3w4eFaPdpBTJcRUgM
  5. select usb in efi loader, and run 'hp unlock'! no files may be shown inside ur usb (pls dont panic man just trust the process)
  6. after success, hold shift, click restart and keep holding shift!
  7. select use a device and select the usb (known as "flash drive")
  8. just wait now, and u will see something that looks like this picture below
:
  1. now, after this wait, it will ask "manufacturer mode to unlock mode": click yes!
  2. now it will boot into windows again, and the usb can be removed. incase windows does not boot, please remove the usb, and wait.
  3. reopen loader, click on hp perm spoof
  4. wait for spoofing process then restart pc

IMPORTANT

if you still need help or struggle to follow these steps, dont hesitate to reach out to us in support.

ASUS SPOOFING

  1. follow this video first: https://streamable.com/k653am
  2. download efi loader: https://mega.nz/file/0C0mzR7T#Ljl83XBVBlvFayHtfZ3dU5aqeO3w4eFaPdpBTJcRUgM
  3. select usb in efi loader, and run secureboot bypass! no files will be shown inside ur usb. that's fine!
  4. open powershell as admin then write ''[guid]::newguid()'' and see the results.
  5. take a picture of the GUID with your phone, we might need it later on (not always).
  6. boot into bios like u did before with tpm and bios configurations. (restart + shift) go to boot > secure boot > os type [windows] & secure boot mode [custom] secure boot mode can be found under "boot configuration" (don't have it? that's fine!)
  7. ensure all default keys are installed. if it shows "0" at all, click "install default keys".
  8. now open 'kek management'
  9. choose "append key" option.
press "no" to load it from a file on external media.
choose usb file system.
choose the "certificate.der" file.
select file format as "public key certificate".
enter the guid (with hyphens) that you saved earlier then press enter. not always!
finally, press "yes" to append kek with content from the .der file.
you should now see a 'success' message if you done everything correctly!
do the same for 'db management' as u did for kek management.
now set your usb as boot priority #1 and windows boot manager as #2.
click save and exit bios again, we are done now. you will boot efi spoofed.
IMPORTANT
if you face any issues during the spoofing process, please reach out to us in tickets and we will try our best to aid you thoroughly
